
// This Hyperlambda code snippet adds a condition to a SQL query using the [add] slot. It targets the [and] node within a [where] clause of a [data.read] operation. The condition uses an [or] logical operator to check if the [ml_requests.prompt] or [ml_requests.completion] fields contain a concatenated string, or if the [ml_requests.user_id] field equals the value of the [filter] argument. This allows for flexible querying based on user input or specific criteria.
add:x:@data.connect/*/data.read/*/where/*/and
   .
      or
         ml_requests.prompt.like:x:@strings.concat
         ml_requests.completion.like:x:@strings.concat
         ml_requests.user_id.eq:x:@.arguments/*/filter
